{{afc comment|1={{ill|Kashima Shrines|ja|鹿島神社}} and {{ill|Katori Shrines|ja|香取神社}} are not common enough to bother making all the articles but making these lists is good because I think a lot of westerners do not understand the sheer quantity of them[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 06:07, 24 March 2025 (UTC)}}
'''Kashima Shrine''' (鹿島神社, [[Kyujitai]]: 鹿嶋神社) is a type of Shinto shrine named "Kashima" dedicated to the deity {{ill|Takemikazuchi|ja|タケミカヅチ}}.
There are approximately 600 Kashima Shrines nationwide, concentrated primarily in the {{ill|Tōhoku region|ja|東北地方}} and the {{ill|Kantō region|ja|関東地方}}, with the head shrine being {{ill|Kashima Jingū|ja|鹿島神宮}} in {{ill|Kashima, Ibaraki|ja|鹿嶋市}}, {{ill|Ibaraki Prefecture|ja|茨城県}}. Most of these shrines were established by inviting the deity from Kashima Jingū, worshipping the same deity, Takemikazuchi.
Takemikazuchi, together with {{ill|Futsunushi|ja|経津主神}} of {{ill|Katori Jingū|ja|香取神宮}} ({{ill|Katori, Chiba|ja|香取市}}, {{ill|Chiba Prefecture|ja|千葉県}}), was revered by the Imperial court and central aristocracy as the ancestral deity of the {{ill|Nakatomi clan|ja|中臣氏}} and {{ill|Fujiwara clan|ja|藤原氏}}. Being a god of martial prowess, Takemikazuchi was also worshipped by samurai families ('''Kashima belief''').
==Tōhoku region== * {{ill|Kashima Shrine (Mashiba, Ichinoseki)|ja|鹿島神社 (一関市真柴)}} (Mashiba, {{ill|Ichinoseki, Iwate|ja|一関市}}, {{ill|Iwate Prefecture|ja|岩手県}}) * {{ill|Kashima Shrine (Ishinomaki)|ja|鹿嶋神社 (石巻市)}} ({{ill|Ishinomaki, Miyagi|ja|石巻市}}, {{ill|Miyagi Prefecture|ja|宮城県}}) * {{ill|Kashima Shrine (Igu District)|ja|鹿島神社 (伊具郡)}} ({{ill|Igu District, Miyagi|ja|伊具郡}}) * {{ill|Kashima Daijingū (Kōriyama)|ja|鹿島大神宮 (郡山市)|lt=Kashima Daijingū|lt_ja=鹿島大神宮}} ({{ill|Kōriyama, Fukushima|ja|郡山市}}, {{ill|Fukushima Prefecture|ja|福島県}}) * {{ill|Kashima Shrine (Shirakawa)|ja|鹿嶋神社 (白河市)|lt=Kashima Shrine|lt_ja=鹿嶋神社}} ({{ill|Shirakawa, Fukushima|ja|白河市}})
==Kantō region== * {{ill|Kashima Shrine (Mashiko)|ja|鹿島神社 (益子町)|lt=Kashima Shrine|lt_ja=鹿島神社}} ({{ill|Mashiko, Tochigi|ja|益子町}}, {{ill|Haga District|ja|芳賀郡}}, {{ill|Tochigi Prefecture|ja|栃木県}}) * {{ill|Kashima Shrine (Fujioka, Tochigi)|ja|鹿島神社 (栃木県栃木市藤岡町部屋)|lt=Kashima Shrine|lt_ja=鹿島神社}} (Fujioka, {{ill|Tochigi City|ja|栃木市}}) * {{ill|Kashima Shrine (Naka)|ja|鹿島神社 (那珂市菅谷)|lt=Kashima Shrine|lt_ja=鹿島神社}} ({{ill|Naka, Ibaraki|ja|那珂市}}) * {{ill|Kashima Shrine (Tsuchiura)|ja|鹿島神社 (土浦市沖宿町)|lt=Kashima Shrine|lt_ja=鹿島神社}} ({{ill|Tsuchiura, Ibaraki|ja|土浦市}}) * {{ill|Kashima Shrine (Hitachinaka)|ja|鹿嶋神社 (ひたちなか市)|lt=Kashima Shrine|lt_ja=鹿嶋神社}} ({{ill|Hitachinaka, Ibaraki|ja|ひたちなか市}}) * {{ill|Sukegawa Kashima Shrine|ja|助川鹿嶋神社}} ({{ill|Hitachi, Ibaraki|ja|日立市}}) * {{ill|Kashima Shrine (Katsuura)|ja|鹿島神社 (勝浦市)|lt=Kashima Shrine|lt_ja=鹿島神社}} ({{ill|Katsuura, Chiba|ja|勝浦市}}) * {{ill|Kashima Shrine (Shinagawa)|ja|鹿嶋神社 (品川区)|lt=Kashima Shrine|lt_ja=鹿嶋神社}} ({{ill|Shinagawa, Tokyo|ja|品川区}}) * {{ill|Kashima Shrine (Edogawa)|ja|鹿島神社 (江戸川区)}} * {{ill|Kashima Shrine (Yokohama)|ja|鹿島神社 (横浜市)|lt=Kashima Shrine|lt_ja=鹿島神社}} ({{ill|Yokohama, Kanagawa|ja|横浜市}}) * {{ill|Kashima Shrine (Sagamihara)|ja|鹿島神社 (相模原市)|lt=Kashima Shrine|lt_ja=鹿島神社}} ({{ill|Sagamihara, Kanagawa|ja|相模原市}}) * {{ill|Kashima Shrine (Yokosuka)|ja|鹿島神社 (横須賀市)}}
